Code.CodeDescription: Day of the Virgin of Guadalupe
Subject matter intended exclusively for specific groups
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: 5J* codes ONLY in exceptional circumstances to indicate the work was specifically and purposefully written or created exclusively for a specific group irrespective of the subject matter. The material does not necessarily have to be specifically ABOUT that group. Often the indication will be part of the heading or brief description of the work. 5J itself can be used with other 5P* Qualifiers if a title is written specifically and exclusively for that group

Code.CodeDescription: Subject matter intended specifically for women and/or girls
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: 5JA codes in exceptional circumstances to indicate the work was specifically and purposefully written or created exclusively FOR women and/or girls, irrespective of the subject matter, for example, Use with: KJMB for a title giving advice on how women can succeed in business leadership, or VFB for a work about personal safety for women. The material does not necessarily have to be specifically ABOUT women and/or girls. N.B. NOT recommended for use with fiction (F* or YF*) codes. DO NOT USE: for marketing purposes to indicate works that might simply or generally be of more interest to women and/or girls than to men and/or boys, nor to indicate the gender of people featured in the work or the gender of the writer

Code.CodeDescription: Subject matter intended specifically for men and/or boys
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: 5JB in exceptional circumstances to indicate the work was specifically and purposefully written or created exclusively FOR men and/or boys, irrespective of the subject matter, for example, Use with: VFJX1 for a title about suicide written for men, or VSPQ for a title for men dealing with male emotions. The material does not necessarily have to be specifically ABOUT men and/or boys. N.B. NOT recommended for use with fiction (F* or YF*) codes. DO NOT USE: for marketing purposes to express a target or expected audience, nor to indicate the gender of character(s) or person(s) featured in the work or the gender of the writer

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to the stages of life
Code.CodeNotes: Use all 5L* codes for: indicating the content of the work has major themes, topics or storylines relating to or specifically about, or from the perspective of, the main stages of life, or the process of ageing, growing up, the cycle of life from birth to death, or fiction done from the point of view of a person or persons of that stage of life. A novel about teenage anxiety could use 5LF, a romance set amongst students at university could use 5LKE, or a book about Yoga for seniors could use 5LKS. DO NOT USE: to indicate a targeted audience for marketing purposes, the content should be primarily about this stage of life or age group or told from the point of view of that age group
Also class here: babies, infants and toddlers. Use for: material that has major or principal themes relating to, or from the perspective of, or primarily about infancy
Use for: material that has major or principal themes relating to, or from the perspective of, or primarily about childhood or being a child, or stories told from the point of view of a child

Use for: material that has major or principal themes relating to, or primarily about the years between childhood and adolescence, the passage from being a child to being a teenager, or stories told from the point of view of the preteen or preadolescence

Also class here: growing from a teenager to being an adult. Use for: material that has major or principal themes relating to, or from the perspective of, or primarily about adolescence or being a teenager, the teenage years, the issues, changes, developments that are common for teenagers. Use with: YF* or F* codes when the main themes of a novel are specifically related to the teenage years, being a teenager, specifically from a teenagers point of view, or issues connected with adolescence and use with non-fiction codes for studies, themes or content about teenagers

Use for: material that has major or principal themes relating to, or from the perspective of, or primarily about being an older teenager (roughly 15 to 19 years old), the later teenage years, the issues, changes, developments that are common for older teenagers, also referred to as young adults in some circumstances, post-adolescents. Use with: YF* or F* codes when the main themes of a novel are specifically related to the later teenage years, being an older teenager, specifically from an older teenager’s point of view, or issues connected with late or post adolescence and use with non-fiction codes for studies, themes or content about older teenagers
Use for: material that has major or principal themes relating to, or from the perspective of, or primarily about adulthood or being an adult, life as an adult, etc

Also class here: post-teens, new adult, young adulthood, twenty something, emerging adulthood, etc. Use for: material that is primarily about, or from the perspective of, or has major or principal themes relating to the stage of life spanning from the late teens through to the mid- or late twenties, often centred on topics around becoming an adult or coming of age, progressing from being a teenager to being an adult, those who are newly adult, learning to become an adult. Use with: FR* for ‘New Adult Romance’ or FRG for ‘College Romance’, FP for ‘New Adult Erotica’, FM* for ‘New Adult Fantasy’, etc. when the main themes of a novel are specifically related to this stage of life and use with non-fiction codes for studies, themes or content about this passage from teenager to adult
Use for: material that has major or principal themes relating to, or from the perspective of, or primarily about midlife or middle age

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to late adulthood / old age
Code.CodeNotes: Also class here: seniors, elders, third agers, retirees, pensioners, older persons. Use for: material that has major or principal themes relating to, or from the perspective of, or primarily about old age or later life. Use with: F* or YF* codes when the main themes of a novel are specifically related to this phase of life, for example, FR* for romance in later life, or YFN for a story about an elderly relative, and use with non-fiction codes for studies, themes or content about this stage of life

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to specific groups and cultures or social and cultural interests
Code.CodeNotes: Use all 5P* codes for: indicating the content of the work has major themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspective of, or are specifically about the particular group of people. DO NOT USE: to indicate a target audience for marketing purposes, nor to identify the origin of the author, unless this relates to the content of the work

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to peoples: ethnic groups, indigenous peoples, cultures and other groupings of people
Code.CodeNotes: Use all 5PB* codes for: for material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspective of, or is about identifiable groups of peoples, either using general or a specific code, when they exist. Use with: PLACE 1* Qualifiers for groups that are associated with a particular geographical area but have no separate code, JBSL* codes for studies relating to a particular group, as appropriate

Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspective of, or about, any groups of people or persons from any of the multiple, diverse and different groups or cultures of the various Indigenous communities, Peoples and Nations and where there is no more precise code. Use with: PLACE 1* Qualifiers as appropriate to indicate location or with LANGUAGE 2* Qualifiers when the language identifies the group, for example, a work about the Indigenous peoples of the Americas, use with 1K, for the Indigenous peoples of Mexico, use with 1KLCM, the Indigenous peoples of Peru, use with 1KLSR, for the Indigenous Peoples of the Arctic use with 1MTN, for Indigenous peoples of Siberia, use with 1FCS, for Indigenous peoples associated with the South -Western US States, use with 1KBB-US-WM, etc, See also: 5PB-US-E 5PB-NZ-A 5PB-AU-A 5PBS

Also class here: Melanesians, Micronesians, Polynesians peoples, including, but not limited to, Kanaks, Papuans, Indigenous Hawaiians, Kānaka Maoli, Fijians, iTaukei, Ni-Vanuatu, Chamorro, Chuukese, Rapa Nui, Samoans, Tahitians. Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, any of the diverse groups of people or persons, who are part of an Indigenous Pacific Island group or heritage

Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, members of any Indigenous community who gained respect and stature through their lives allowing them to have a leadership role

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to peoples or groups of multiple heritage / culture
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material where the major or principal themes, topics or storylines relate to, or from the perspectives of, or are about any of the diverse groups of people or persons of multiple heritage or cultures

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to migrant groups / diaspora communities or peoples / groups with shared heritage
Code.CodeNotes: Use all 5PBC* codes for: material where the major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, (historical and recent) diverse groups of people or persons who have migrated or were exiled or displaced from one part of the world to another; or are part of a diaspora community and who maintain a strong and distinct identity and cultural shared heritage associated with another geographical or cultural area within their present place of residence. Use all 5PBC* codes with: PLACE 1* Qualifiers as appropriate, to indicate the geographical area that is the subject of the work, usually where that group is now, for example, a title about Syrian migrant communities in Sweden, use with 1DNS, or a title about Guatemalan migrant workers in Mexico, use with 1KLCM or a study of German exiled writers of the mid-twentieth century, in the USA, use with 1KBB, See also: 5PBD

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to people of the Middle Eastern diasporas / heritage
Code.CodeNotes: Also class here: diaspora peoples of Western Asia, Anatolia, the Arabian Peninsula. Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, (historical and recent) Middle Eastern diasporas, or any of the diverse groups or individuals of Middle Eastern heritage living in another geographical area or culture. Use with: PLACE 1* Qualifiers as appropriate, to indicate the scope of the geographical area covered by the group or individual or topic in the work, for example, a biography of an Armenian family in France, use with 1DDF*, or a novel about Turkish migrants in Germany, use with 1DFG*, or a history of Arab Americans in Detroit, use with 1KBB-US-MLGD. Prefer: 1FB* PLACE qualifiers, without 5PBCB, for works about peoples, groups or individuals who live in a particular Middle Eastern country or region, or works about peoples of the Middle East, See also: 1FB*

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to people of the North African / Maghreb diasporas / heritage
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, (historical and recent) North African diasporas or any of the diverse groups or individuals of North African or Maghrebian heritage living in another geographical area or culture. Use with: PLACE 1* Qualifiers as appropriate, to indicate the scope of the geographical area covered by the group or individual or topic in the work, for example, a novel dealing with the experience of being Kabyle in the suburbs of Lyon, use with 1DDF-FR-VFA. Prefer: 1HB* PLACE qualifiers without 5PBCD for works about peoples, groups or individuals who live in a particular North African country or region, or works about peoples of North Africa, See also: 5PBD 1HB*

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to people of the South Asian diasporas / heritage
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, (historical and recent) South Asian diasporas, or any of the diverse groups or individuals of South Asian heritage living in another geographical area or culture. Use with: PLACE 1* Qualifiers as appropriate, to indicate the scope of the geographical area covered by the group or individual or topic in the work, for example, a teen novel about a Tamil Australian, use with 1MBF or a book about desi music in the USA use with 1KBB. Prefer: 1FK* PLACE qualifiers without 5PBCG for works about peoples, groups or individuals who live in a particular South Asian country or region, or works about peoples of South Asia, See also: 1FK*

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to people of the South East Asian diasporas / heritage
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, (historical and recent) South East Asian diaspora or any of the diverse groups or individuals of South East Asian heritage living in another geographical area or culture. Use with: PLACE 1* Qualifiers as appropriate, to indicate the scope of the geographical area covered by the group or individual or topic in the work, for example, a picture book about overseas Vietnamese family in California, use with 1KBB-US-WPC or a study of the Hmong people who migrated to Thailand, use with 1FMT. Prefer: 1FM* PLACE qualifiers without 5PBCH for works about peoples, groups or individuals who live in a particular South East Asian country or region, or works about peoples of South East Asia, See also: 1FM*

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to people of the East Asian diasporas / heritage
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, (historical and recent) East Asian diasporas or any of the diverse groups or individuals of East Asian heritage living in another geographical area or culture. Use with: PLACE 1* Qualifiers as appropriate, to indicate the scope of the geographical area covered by the group or individual or topic in the work, for example, a story about Korean Canadians in Toronto, use with 1KBC-CA-OSM or a work about Chinese Peruvians, use with 1KLSR. Prefer: 1FP* PLACE qualifiers without 5PBCJ for works about peoples, groups or individuals who live in a particular East Asian country or region, or works about peoples of East Asia, See also: 1FP*

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to people of the Pacific Island diasporas / heritage
Code.CodeNotes: Also class here: Pasifika, Pacific Peoples, South Sea Islanders. Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about,(historical and recent) Pacific Islander diasporas or any of the diverse groups or individuals who identify as being of Pacific Island heritage living in another geographical area or culture. Use with: PLACE 1* Qualifiers as appropriate, to indicate the scope of the geographical area covered by the group or individual or topic in the work, for example, a study of Samoan Australians in Brisbane, use with 1MBF-AU-QB. Prefer: 1M* PLACE qualifiers without 5PBCL for works about peoples, groups or individuals who live in a particular Pacific country or region, or works about peoples of the Pacific Islands or Oceania, See also: 5PB-NZ-A 1M*

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to people of the Caribbean diasporas / heritage
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, (historical and recent) Caribbean diasporas or any of the diverse groups or individuals of Caribbean heritage living in another geographical area or culture. Use with: PLACE 1* Qualifiers as appropriate, to indicate the scope of the geographical area covered by the group or individual or topic in the work, for example, a memoir about a person of Jamaican heritage growing up in New York, use with 1KBB-US-NAKC. Prefer: 1KJ* PLACE qualifiers without 5PBCM for works about peoples, groups or individuals who live in a particular Caribbean country or region, or works about peoples of the Caribbean, See also: 1KJ*

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to people of the Latin American diasporas / heritage
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, (historical and recent) Latin American diasporas or any of the diverse groups or individuals of Latin American heritage living in another geographical area or culture. Use with: PLACE 1* Qualifiers as appropriate, to indicate the scope of the geographical area covered by the group or individual or topic in the work, for example, a study of Mexican Britons living in London use with 1DDU-GB-ESL or a work about Colombians in Spain, use with 1DSE. Prefer: 1KL* PLACE qualifiers without 5PBCN for works about peoples, groups or individuals who live in a particular Latin American country or region, or works about peoples of Latin America, See also: 5PB-US-H 1KL*

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to people of the North American diasporas / heritage
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, (historical and recent) North American diasporas, or any of the diverse groups or individuals of North American heritage living in another geographical area or culture. Use with: PLACE 1* Qualifiers as appropriate, to indicate the scope of the geographical area covered by the group or individual or topic in the work. Prefer: 1K* PLACE qualifiers without 5PBCP for works about peoples, groups or individuals who live in a particular North American country or region or works about peoples of North America, See also: 1K*

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to people of the European diasporas / heritage
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or is about, (historical and recent) European diasporas, or any of the diverse groups or individuals of European heritage living in another geographical area or culture. Use with: PLACE 1* Qualifiers as appropriate, to indicate the scope of the geographical area covered by the group or individual or topic in the work, for example, a novel about an Albanian migrant in Helsinki use with 1DNF-FI-CB or the history of the Irish in Boston, use with 1KBB-US-NEMB. Prefer: 1D* PLACE qualifiers without 5PBCQ for works about peoples, groups or individuals who live in a particular European country or region, or works about peoples of Europe, See also: 1D*

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to people of the African diasporas / heritage
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, (historical and recent) African diasporas – that is the worldwide collection of communities descended from Africans or sub-Saharan Africa’s peoples or any of the diverse groups or individuals of African heritage living in another geographical area or culture. Use with: PLACE 1* Qualifiers as appropriate to indicate the scope of the geographical area covered by the group or individual or topic in the work, for example, with 1KBC for Black Canadians, 1KJ* for Afro-Caribbean, 1D* for Afro-Europeans, 1KLSB for Afro-Brazilians, with 1KL for a work on Afro-descendants in Latin America. etc. Prefer: 1H* PLACE qualifiers without 5PBD for works about peoples, groups or individuals who live in a particular African country or region, or works about peoples of Africa, See also: 5PBC* 5PBCD 5PB-GB-B 5PB-US-C 5PB-CA-G 1H*
Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, Kurds or Kurdish persons or groups
Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, any of the diverse nomadic groups, peoples or persons

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to Romani people and Travellers
Code.CodeNotes: Also class here: the Roma, Romani diaspora, Romanichal, Kale and Romany communities. Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, Romani persons or groups. Use with: PLACE 1* Qualifiers as appropriate, to indicate the work is about the Romani people or Travellers of a particular country or region.
Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, Sami persons or groups, See also: 5PBA

Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, any of the diverse groups, peoples or persons from Arab world or the Arab diaspora

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to First Nations peoples in Australia
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, persons or groups from any of the multiple, diverse and different groups or cultures of the various First nations of Australia, See also: 5PBA

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to Australian South Sea Islanders

Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, persons or groups from any of the multiple, diverse and different groups or cultures of the various Indigenous Peoples and Nations largely within the boundaries of the present-day Canada

Also class here: Peoples of arctic and subarctic regions, including the Inupiaq and Yupik, Kalaallit, Yuit. Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, persons or groups from any of the Inuit groups or cultures in the circumpolar region of present-day Canada, Alaska, Greenland, or Siberia

Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, persons or groups from the Métis nations and peoples in Canada and in North America

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to Black Canadians / African-Canadian and Caribbean-Canadian people
Code.CodeNotes: Also class here: Afro-Canadians, Canadians of African or Afro-Caribbean descent. Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, any of the diverse groups, peoples or persons of African or Afro-Caribbean heritage in Canada. Prefer: 5PBD for material about diaspora groups or peoples of African heritage or 5PBCM for Caribbean heritage or 5PBCN for Latin American or 5PBCB for North African or Maghrebi heritage in other countries, See also: 5PBD 5PBCM 5PBCN 5PBCB

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to Latin American Canadian people
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, any of the diverse groups, peoples or persons of Latin American heritage in Canada. Prefer: 5PBC* qualifiers for material about diaspora groups or peoples of Latin American heritage in other countries, See also: 5PBC*

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to Arab or Middle Eastern Canadian people
Code.CodeNotes: Also class here: Arab Canadians, West Asian Canadians. Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, any of the diverse groups, peoples or persons of Arab, Middle Eastern or West Asian heritage in Canada

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to East Asian Canadian people
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, any of the diverse groups, peoples or persons of East Asian heritage in Canada

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to South Asian Canadian people
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, any of the diverse groups, peoples or persons of South Asian heritage in Canada

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to Southeast Asian Canadian people
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, any of the diverse groups, peoples or persons of Southeast Asian heritage in Canada

Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, any of the diverse groups, peoples or persons of European heritage in Canada

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to Minority Ethnic or ethnically diverse peoples and groups of the UK
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material where the major or principal themes, topics or storylines relate to, or are from the perspective of, or are about, the broad and ethnically diverse communities, groups or peoples referenced under terms like ethnic minorities, global majority, BAME or similar in the UK. Prefer: more specific 5PB-GB* codes when or other 5PB* qualifiers as appropriate for material about specific British communities, groups or individuals, for example with 5PBCB for British people of Middle Eastern heritage or 5PB-AA-A for British Arabs, or 5PBB for people or groups of multiple heritages, See also: 5PBD 5PBC* 5PB-GB*

Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, any of the diverse groups, peoples or persons of Asian heritage in the UK

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to British East and Southeast Asian people
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, any of the diverse groups, peoples or persons of East or Southeastern Asian heritage in the UK, See also: 5PBCJ

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to British South Asian people
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, any of the diverse groups, peoples or persons of South Asian heritage in the UK, See also: 5PBCG

Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, any of the diverse groups, peoples or persons of Black heritage in the UK

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to Black British Caribbean people
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, any of the diverse groups, peoples or persons of Black Caribbean or Afro-Caribbean heritage in the UK, See also: 5PBCM

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to Black British African people
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, any of the diverse groups, peoples or persons of Black African heritage in the UK, See also: 5PBD
Also class here: Italo-Albanians
See also: 5PBA 5PBCL

Also class here: Hutterites. Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, groups and people associated with the Mennonites or Amish churches or communities in any country. Use with: PLACE 1* Qualifiers as appropriate, for works about Amish or Mennonite in Canada use with 1KBC* or for the USA use with 1KBB, for Mexico use with 1KLCM, etc

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to African American / Black American people
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspective of, or about, any of the diverse groups, peoples or persons of Black American heritage in the United States of America and its territories. Prefer: 5PBD for material about diaspora groups or peoples of Sub-Saharan and Black African heritage in other countries, See also: 5PBD 5PBCM

Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspective of, or about, any of the diverse groups, peoples or persons of Asian or Asian Pacific heritage in the United States of America and its territories. Prefer: 5PBC* qualifiers for material about diaspora groups or peoples of Pacific or Asian heritage in other countries, See also: 5PBC*

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to Pacific Islander American people
Code.CodeNotes: Also class here: Native Hawaiians, Samoan Americans, Chamorro, Melanesian Americans, Micronesian Americans, Polynesian Americans. Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, any of the diverse groups, peoples or persons of Pacific Island heritage in the United States of America and its territories. Prefer: 5PBCL qualifiers for material about diaspora groups or peoples of Pacific Island heritage in other countries, See also: 5PBCL

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to Native American people / First Americans
Code.CodeNotes: Also class here: Alaska Natives. Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspective of, or about, persons or groups from any of the multiple, diverse and different groups or cultures of the various Indigenous peoples and Nations largely within the boundaries of the present-day United States of America and its territories. Prefer: 5PBA plus the most appropriate PLACE 1* qualifier for works relating to the Indigenous peoples of in the Americas or particular areas of the Americas, such as Mexico, Peru or Bolivia, See also: 5PBA 5PB-CA-A
Use with: PLACE 1* Qualifiers as appropriate
Also class here: Louisiana Acadians, Cadjins

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to Latin / Hispanic US American people
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, any of the diverse groups, peoples or persons of Latin American heritage in the United States of America and it’s territories. Prefer: 5PBC* qualifiers for material about diaspora groups or peoples of Latin American heritage in other countries, See also: 5PBCN 5PBCM 5PB-CA-H

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to Middle Eastern and Arab Americans
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, any of the diverse groups, peoples or persons of Arab or Middle Eastern heritage in the United States of America and its territories

Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, any of the diverse groups, peoples or persons of European heritage in the United States of America and its territories

Also class here: Altai, Bashkirs, Chuvash, Crimean Tatars, Gagauz, Kazakhs, Kyrgyz, Turkmens, Tuvans, Uyghurs, Uzbeks, Volga Tatars, Yakuts. Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, any of the diverse groups, peoples or persons (both historical and actual), who use a Turkic language or are of Turkic heritage

Also class here: Imazighen. Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, any of the diverse groups, peoples or persons (both historical and actual) who use an Amazigh (Berber) language or are of Amazigh (Berber) heritage. Use with: 5PBCD for works about diaspora communities

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to specific socioeconomic groups / status
Code.CodeNotes: Use all 5PD* codes for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspective of, or about, social stratification of groups of people or persons based on factors like birth, wealth, income, education, occupation, social status, social or political power, class, etc, or equivalent terminology, and the relative social position within social groups or categories, geographical areas, etc

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to lower socioeconomic groups / status
Code.CodeNotes: Also class here: working class, labouring classes, economically disadvantaged, the precariat, etc. Use for: qualifying works that examine or explore the concept of the ‘lower classes’ based on various socioeconomic concepts or that examine aspects of class or status in relation to other subjects, either as a general topic or from a personal point of view, or look at the groups of people or persons who hold the lowest social status, are often the poorest members of a class society, or may wield the least power or influence

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to middle socioeconomic groups / status
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: works that examine or explore the concept of the ‘middle classes’ based on various socioeconomic concepts or examine aspects of class or status in relation to other subjects either as a general topic or from a personal point of view, or look at the groups of people or persons who are in the middle of socioeconomic hierarchies

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to higher socioeconomic groups / status
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: works that examine or explore the concept of the ‘upper classes’ based on various socioeconomic concepts or examine aspects of class or status in relation to other subjects either as a general topic or from a personal point of view, or look at the groups of people or persons who hold the highest social status, are often the wealthiest members of a class society, or wield the greatest political, economic or social power or influence

Also class here: Royals, Royal families, Kings, Queens, Princesses, Princes, Emperors, Empresses, Aristocrats, Nobility, Nobles, etc. Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about, people, families, dynasties or groups, who have high socioeconomic status based on a usually hereditary title associated with royalty or nobility

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to the very rich and wealthy
Code.CodeNotes: Also class here: Billionaires, High-net-worth individuals, ultra-rich people, extremely wealthy people, wealthy elites, groups of wealthy people. Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about, people, families, dynasties or groups, who have high socioeconomic status based on very high wealth or economic power

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to presidents, prime ministers, political leaders
Code.CodeNotes: Also class here: Political elites, people with high status based on political power, heads of state, dictators, autocrats. Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about, people, families, dynasties or groups, who have high socioeconomic status based on a political position, political power or a role of leadership of a political entity of some sort

Use all 5PG* codes for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or is about religious people, individuals, groups or cultures; or about a specific religious group; or material adapted for a religious group. Use with: JBSR as well as other subjects, fiction and non-fiction. For items purely about the specific religion, i.e. classed with QR* codes, these qualifiers are not necessary

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to Confucian people and groups
Relating to Hindu people and groups
Relating to Sikh people and groups
Relating to Buddhist people and groups
Relating to Jewish people and groups
Relating to Christian people and groups
Relating to Druze people and groups
Relating to Islamic / Muslim people and groups
Relating to Shinto people and groups
Relating to Taoist people and groups
Relating to particular relationship, family or kinship types
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about, people or groups in a particular type of relationship or kinship
Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about, family or families of any type or form
Also class here: brothers, sisters. Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about, siblings
Also class here: mothers, fathers. Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about, parents
Also class here: grandmothers, grandfathers. Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about, grandparents

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to alternative, blended or recomposed families
Code.CodeNotes: Also class here: Stepfamilies, reconstituted family. Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about any form of alternative family

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to single parents / single parent families
Code.CodeNotes: Also class here: single mothers, single fathers. Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about, single parents or single parent families

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to chosen families / found families
Code.CodeNotes: Also class here: chosen family, found family, families of choice. Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about, chosen families or about any non-biologically related group of people established to provide ongoing social support

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to people with visible or hidden disabilities, impairments or conditions
Code.CodeNotes: Use all 5PM* codes for: indicating the content of the work has major themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspective of, or specifically about people, groups or individuals

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to people with mobility or physical disabilities or impairments
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about, people who have any form of physiological, functional and/or mobility condition, disability or impairment, including wheelchair users, absent limb / reduced limb function, Spinal Cord Disability, etc

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to people with visual disabilities or impairments
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about, people who have a visual disability, condition or impairment, such as loss of sight, blindness, low vision, sight or eye conditions, people living with little or no sight, blind and partially sighted people, people affected by sight loss

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to people with speech, language or communication impairments or disorders
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about, people who have a speech condition, impairment, impediment or disorder, such as stuttering, stammering, apraxia, dysarthria, selective mutism, articulation errors, Social (pragmatic) communication disorder, Speech sound disorder, childhood-onset fluency disorder

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to people with hearing disabilities or impairments
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about, people who have a auditory sensory condition, disability or impairment, such as loss of hearing, deafness, Deaf persons

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to people with motor disorders or conditions
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about, people who have a disorder of the nervous system or a neurodevelopmental motor disorder, including tic disorders, Tourette syndrome, Developmental coordination disorder, Stereotypic movement disorder, Motor neuron disease, etc

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to people on the autism spectrum
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about, autistic persons or to people with autism, people with Asperger’s

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to people with learning disorders, difficulties or disabilities
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about, people with learning or reading disorders or difficulties, including dyspraxia, dyslexia, hyperlexia, alexia, dyscalculia, dysgraphia, aphasia, dysphasia, auditory processing disorder, language processing disorder, learning disabilities or disorders in language, speech, motor skills, writing, maths, reading comprehension, word decoding, etc

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to people with Attention Deficit Hyperactivity Disorder (ADHD)
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about, people who have ADHD

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to people with Down syndrome
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about, people or persons with Down syndrome or trisomy 21

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to people with cerebral palsy
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about, people or persons with cerebral palsy spectrum disorder

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to people with degenerative conditions
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about, people with degenerative conditions, such as Parkinson’s disease, Multiple sclerosis, Motor neurone disease, etc

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to people with dementia / Alzheimer’s
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about, people who have syndromes or conditions associated with an ongoing decline of brain functioning, like vascular dementia, Alzheimer‘s disease

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to people with hidden or invisible disabilities / disorders
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about, people with hidden disabilities – mental or physical – that is any disabilities, disorders or challenges that are not immediately apparent to others

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to people with mood disorders / affective disorders
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about, people who have a mood disorders, such as Bipolar disorder, cyclothymia, disruptive mood dysregulation disorder, dysthymia, major depressive disorders, clinical depression, premenstrual dysphoric disorder, seasonal affective disorder

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to people with Albinism or Hypopigmentation
Relates specifically to the life experience of women or girls
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about the experience of being woman or girl, or aspects of womanhood, femininity, girlhood etc. DO NOT USE: as an audience code for marketing purposes to express a target audience, nor to indicate the gender of the creator, nor simply to indicate the gender of the main character

Code.CodeDescription: Relates specifically to the life experience of men or boys
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about the experience of being a man or boy, or aspects of manhood, masculinity, boyhood etc. DO NOT USE: as an audience code for marketing purposes to express a target audience, nor to indicate the gender of the creator, nor simply to indicate the gender of the main character

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to particular subcultures, subcultural groups, or communities
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about particular alternative lifestyle groups, or particular subcultural groups or individuals, within a cultural society that differentiates itself from the conservative and standard values to which it belongs, and often with their own norms and values regarding cultural, political, and sexual matters

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to BDSM and other erotic subcultures
Code.CodeNotes: Also class here: Bondage and discipline, Dominance and submission, sadism and masochism, sexual fetishism, sexual or erotic roleplay, or other risk-aware consensual kinks, or fetish fashions, subcultures or group such as leather subculture, rubber or latex fetishism, PVC, spandex, uniforms, sportswear fetishism etc. Use for: stories, true accounts, sociological approaches, photography or any content that relates to BDSM or sexual fetishism or material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about particular erotic subcultures

Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, the members of the broad and diverse LGBTQIAP2S+, LGBTIQA+SB or queer community or specific groups or persons who identify with the term, or variations of it, where there is not a more specific qualifier code. Use with: other subjects as appropriate, such as JBSJ, YXB, YF*, XQ*, V*, F* codes etc. For works specifically about LGBTQ+ Pride Festivals use with 5HDG. Prefer: more specific categories for works relating specifically to lesbian, gay, bisexual, pansexual, polysexual, asexual, intersex, non-binary, genderfluid or trans people

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to bisexual / pansexual / polysexual people
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has major or principal themes relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, bisexual, omnisexual, polysexual or pansexual people, persons or groups or material about persons who identify with any variants of these terms. Use with: other subjects as appropriate, such as JBSJ, YXB, F*, YF*, XQ* codes, etc

Use for: material that has major or principal themes relating to, or from the perspectives of, or about, people or persons or groups who are gay or identify as gay. Use with: other subjects as appropriate, such as JBSJ, YXB, F*, YF*, XQ* codes, etc

Use for: material that has major or principal themes relating to, from the perspectives of, or about, people or persons or groups who are lesbians or identify as lesbians. Use with: other subjects as appropriate, such as JBSJ, YXB, F*, YF*, XQ* codes, etc

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to Trans / Transgender people or gender minorities
Code.CodeNotes: Also class here: transsexual, transgender, gender minority, third gender, X-gender, Hijra, etc. Use for: material that has major or principal themes relating to, from the perspectives of, or about, those whose gender is different (wholly or partially) from that assigned to them at birth, or gender variance in cultures which have established more than two genders; or material about persons who identify with any variants of these terms. Use with: other subjects as appropriate, such as JBSF3, YXB, F*, V* codes etc
Also class here: Non-binary gender identities, identities outside the gender binary, genderqueer, enby, gender non-conforming, non-binary, genderfluid
Use for: material that has themes relating to, or is about intersex, or people with intersex variations or traits

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to asexual or aromantic people
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material that has themes relating to, or is about asexual and/or aromantic people, or people in the Ace community, or topics around asexuality, grey asexuality or material about persons who identify with any variants of these terms

Use for: material that has major or principal themes, topics or storylines relating to, from the perspective of, or about particular people, persons or groups who identify using Indigenous concepts of gender roles, gender identity or sexuality. Use with: other 5P* Qualifiers as appropriate

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to specific and significant cultural interests
Code.CodeNotes: Use all 5PX* codes for: topics that are not covered elsewhere but are significantly used in national book supply chains and cannot be expressed using core codes and qualifiers. NB: 5PX may be used but further information should be included in descriptive metadata as to why this qualifier is being included
Use for: any title that could be put into a ‘Shakespeare’ section

Use with: any subject code to indicate works that are about or inspired by Arthur or the literature of the ‘Matter of Britain’, and the associated legends, characters, traditions, histories or themes, for example, with FN* or YFJ or YFH* codes Arthurian fantasy fiction

Code.CodeDescription: Literature of a country, territory or region (NOT used for setting)
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: works of contemporary or historic written or oral literature (fiction, poetry, prose, drama, etc) widely regarded, or presented as being part of the literature of a place, usually because the work is widely associated or identified with a place or the culture of a particular region, country, or territory. Use with: other codes as appropriate for particular types of literature, such as DB* for classic literature, DC* for poetry, DD* for drama, FBA for contemporary literature, FBC for classic works of fiction, FYT for literature in translation, other F* codes for genre fiction, WTL* for travel literature, Y* codes for children’s or teenage literature, X* codes for comic books, etc. Prefer: PLACE 1* Qualifiers for the setting of a narrative. DO NOT USE: to indicate setting of a novel, Country of publication (in other metadata), language of the contents (in other metadata),the place of residence of an author, (in other metadata), etc. DO NOT USE: 5T itself - always use 5T* codes, See also: 1*

Code.CodeDescription: Contains explicit or offensive material or content
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: titles featuring scenes or vocabulary, that could cause offence or upset an unaware reader, usually of a sexual or violent or discriminatory nature, and therefore only suitable for a relatively mature teen or an adult audience and where it is considered important that any potential reader is made aware that the content may not be suitable for all. NB: If using 5X with a Y* code it is highly recommended that an explanation of the reason for using it be sent in a descriptive text elsewhere in the titles metadata and that a suitable 5A * Age qualifier be used

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to special / particular aspects of the content
Code.CodeNotes: Use all 5Y* codes for: describing a specific and very particular aspect of the content (not the format) of a title, that is not covered by other qualifiers. DO NOT USE: 5Y itself - always use 5Y* codes

Use for: works that are purposefully written to actively challenge a gender stereotype or norm around gender roles or includes positive representation of non-stereotypical gender roles, e.g. YBC* or YF* codes for children’s stories. NB: Further details of why this qualifier is being used should be sent in other descriptive metadata

Code.CodeDescription: Content relating to body acceptance / body positivity
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: works that encourage body acceptance or body neutrality, that show a diverse range of body types, sizes, shapes, that show positive roles for characters, people, or groups of different body types

Code.CodeDescription: Content relates specifically to anthropomorphic characters
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: content that has anthropomorphic characters or uses anthropomorphism as a literary device to tell a story, content that has stories that use the attribution of human traits, emotions, or intentions to non-human entities, such as animals or plants

Code.CodeDescription: Content relates specifically to multiple perspectives
Code.CodeNotes: Also class here: multiperspectivity, polyperspectivity. Use for: content that is shown from more than one perspective, for fiction that uses multiple narrators or a multiple narrative, or for non-fiction where the subject or events are evaluated from multiple different perspectives or points of view

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to UN Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs)
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: works where the contents are specifically about or advance some or all of the UN SDG goals or the title is part of a SDG Book Club list

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to UN SDG 1 - Ending Poverty
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: works where the contents are specifically about, advance some of the ideas or explore SDG 1 - Ending poverty in all its forms everywhere. (See https://sdgs.un.org/goals/goal1)

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to UN SDG 2 - Zero Hunger
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: works where the contents are specifically about, advance some of the ideas or explore SDG 2 - End hunger, achieve food security and improved nutrition and promote sustainable agriculture. (See https://sdgs.un.org/goals/goal2)

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to UN SDG 3 - Good Health and Well-Being
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: works where the contents are specifically about, advance some of the ideas or explore SDG 3 - Ensure healthy lives and promote well-being for all at all ages. (See https://sdgs.un.org/goals/goal3)

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to UN SDG 4 - Quality Education
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: works where the contents are specifically about, advance some of the ideas or explore SDG 4 - Ensure inclusive and equitable quality education and promote lifelong learning opportunities for all. (See https://sdgs.un.org/goals/goal4)

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to UN SDG 5 - Gender Equality
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: works where the contents are specifically about, advance some of the ideas or explore SDG 5 - Achieve gender equality and empower all women and girls. (See https://sdgs.un.org/goals/goal5)

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to UN SDG 6 - Clean Water and Sanitation
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: works where the contents are specifically about, advance some of the ideas or explore SDG 6 - Ensure availability and sustainable management of water and sanitation for all. (See https://sdgs.un.org/goals/goal6)

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to UN SDG 7 - Affordable and Clean Energy
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: works where the contents are specifically about, advance some of the ideas or explore SDG 7 - Ensure access to affordable, reliable, sustainable and modern energy for all. (See https://sdgs.un.org/goals/goal7)

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to UN SDG 8 - Decent Work and Economic Growth
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: works where the contents are specifically about, advance some of the ideas or explore SDG 8 - Promote sustained, inclusive and sustainable economic growth, full and productive employment and decent work for all. (See https://sdgs.un.org/goals/goal8)

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to UN SDG 9 - Industry, Innovation and Infrastructure
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: works where the contents are specifically about, advance some of the ideas or explore SDG 9 - Build resilient infrastructure, promote inclusive and sustainable industrialization and foster innovation. (See https://sdgs.un.org/goals/goal9)

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to UN SDG 10 - Reduced Inequalities
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: works where the contents are specifically about, advance some of the ideas or explore SDG 10 - Reduce inequality within and among countries. (See https://sdgs.un.org/goals/goal10)

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to UN SDG 11 - Sustainable Cities and Communities
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: works where the contents are specifically about, advance some of the ideas or explore SDG 11 - Make cities and human settlements inclusive, safe, resilient and sustainable. (See https://sdgs.un.org/goals/goal11)

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to UN SDG 12 - Responsible Consumption and Production
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: works where the contents are specifically about, advance some of the ideas or explore SDG 12 - Ensure sustainable consumption and production patterns. (See https://sdgs.un.org/goals/goal12)

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to UN SDG 13 - Climate Action
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: works where the contents are specifically about, advance some of the ideas or explore SDG 13 - Take urgent action to combat climate change and its impacts. (See https://sdgs.un.org/goals/goal13)

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to UN SDG 14 - Life Below Water
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: works where the contents are specifically about, advance some of the ideas or explore SDG 14 - Conserve and sustainably use the oceans, seas and marine resources for sustainable development. (See https://sdgs.un.org/goals/goal14)

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to UN SDG 15 - Life on Land
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: works where the contents are specifically about, advance some of the ideas or explore SDG 15 - Protect, restore and promote sustainable use of terrestrial ecosystems, sustainably manage forests, combat desertification, and halt and reverse land degradation and halt biodiversity loss. (See https://sdgs.un.org/goals/goal15)

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to UN SDG 16 - Peace, Justice and Strong Institutions
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: works where the contents are specifically about, advance some of the ideas or explore SDG 16 - Promote peaceful and inclusive societies for sustainable development, provide access to justice for all and build effective, accountable and inclusive institutions at all levels. (See https://sdgs.un.org/goals/goal16)

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to UN SDG 17 - Partnerships for Goals
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: works where the contents are specifically about, advance some of the ideas or explore SDG 17 - Strengthen the means of implementation and revitalize the Global Partnership for Sustainable Development. (See https://sdgs.un.org/goals/goal17)
